Interface PolicyFinder

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    PolicyFinderImpl

    public interface PolicyFinder
    Global dependency for finding Policy and PolicyPeriod entities.

    • Method Detail

      • findMostRecentBoundPeriodByPolicy

        PolicyPeriod findMostRecentBoundPeriodByPolicy(Policy policy)
        Returns the most recently promoted PolicyPeriod belonging to policy for the latest policy term (which may be in the future), or null if none exists. Of the policy term that has the latest policy term start date, this method returns the period with the flag indicating it is the most recent model.
        Parameters:
        policy - the policy to get the most recent bound period for
        Returns:
        the most recently bound period of the policy

      • findLocalPoliciesByAccount

        IQueryBeanResult<Policy> findLocalPoliciesByAccount(Account account)
        Gets all Policy objects stored in the local database that have a foreign key to account.
        Parameters:
        account - the account to get policies for
        Returns:
        policies for the given account

      • findPolicyByPolicyNumber

        Policy findPolicyByPolicyNumber(java.lang.String policyNumber)
        Returns the Policy which has a period with the given policy number, or null if no such policy is found.
        Parameters:
        policyNumber - the policy number for which you want the policy
        Returns:
        policy matching the given number, or null if none found

      • findMostRecentBoundPeriodByPolicyNumber

        PolicyPeriod findMostRecentBoundPeriodByPolicyNumber(java.lang.String policyNumber)
        Returns the most recent bound PolicyPeriod for the given policy number for the term that has the latest policy term start date. This searches all periods on the policy, so the PolicyNumber of the result period may be different from the original argument. Returns null if no bound period is found.
        Parameters:
        policyNumber - identifier for the policy for which we want the most recent period
        Returns:
        the most recent bound period or null if no policy matches the given number

      • findMostRecentBoundPeriodByPolicyPeriod

        PolicyPeriod findMostRecentBoundPeriodByPolicyPeriod(PolicyPeriod period)
        Returns the most recent bound PolicyPeriod for the given policy period (the latest period with the same PeriodID as the passed-in period). Returns null if no bound period is found.
        Parameters:
        period - the period for which we want to find the most recent bound period
        Returns:
        the most recent bound period associated with the policy associated with the given period

      • findPolicyPeriodByPolicyNumberAndAsOfDate

        PolicyPeriod findPolicyPeriodByPolicyNumberAndAsOfDate(java.lang.String policyNumber,
                                                       java.util.Date asOfDate)
        Returns the most recent bound PolicyPeriod whose policy number is policyNumber and is effective as of asOfDate, or null if none exists. The period will be sliced as of asOfDate.
        Parameters:
        policyNumber - the policy number to match
        asOfDate - the date to be checked
        Returns:
        the period for a policy matching the given number effective as of the given date, or null if no match

      • findPolicyPeriodByPolicyAndAsOfDate

        PolicyPeriod findPolicyPeriodByPolicyAndAsOfDate(Policy policy,
                                                 java.util.Date asOfDate)
        Returns the most recently promoted PolicyPeriod belonging to policy which is effective as of asOfDate, or null if none exists. The period will be sliced as of asOfDate.
        Parameters:
        policy - the policy to be checked
        asOfDate - the date to be checked
        Returns:
        the policy period for the given policy as of the given date, or null if none match

      • findPolicyByPublicId

      • findPolicyPeriodByPublicId

        Parameters:
        publicId - the public ID of the desired PolicyPeriod
        Returns:
        the period with the given public ID, or returns null if none match
